        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 5:12AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 512 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 5 miles west of Cloudy, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Clayton Lake State Park...        Stanley...
Sardis...                         Snow...
Nashoba...                        Kiamichi...
Albion...                         Dunbar...
Finley...                         Tuskahoma...
Cloudy...                         Clayton...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
